Business Brief -- Mesa Airlines Inc.:
   Terms of Planned Merger
   With WestAir Are Revised
The price of Mesa shares which will determine the final
ratio will be the average between the bid and ask price of
Mesa common stock over the last 10 trading days prior to
Mesa's annual shareholder meeting on May 14.
   The merger between Mesa, which flies out of Albuquerque,
N.M., and Phoenix, Ariz., and WestAir, which flies out of San
Francisco, Los Angeles, Seattle and Portland, Ore., is
planned to be closed in late May or early June.